    "Background": {
      "text": "Nephritic syndrome, form of chronic\nglomerulonephritis\ncaused by deposition of IgA immune complexes in glomeruli\nSlowly progressive",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "glomerulonephritis",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Glomerulonephritis"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Hematuria\n, persistent or recurrent, macroscopic or asymptomatic microscopic\nGross hematuria initially begins a few days after febrile illness, thus mimicking acute postinfectious glomerulonephritis\nMild\nproteinuria\n+/-\nflank pain\n,\nfever\nduring acute episodes\nUsually slowly progressive, but rapidly progressive glomerulonephritis manifests initially in <10% of patients",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
